hopobject.body: I've got a very weak signal anavar dosage pre contest George Wilfred Proudfoot was born in Co Durham on December 19 1921. His grandfather was a miner; his father killed 13 Germans single-handed in the First World War and told his alcoholic CO: “Throw that whisky bottle away or I’ll shoot you.” Wilfred was educated at Crook council school and Scarborough College. As a boy he revelled in tales of the French Foreign Legion and longed to see the Sahara; when he finally got there, in 1966, it was raining.
